-- Queensland State Declares Disaster as Floods Force Evacuations
-- B y   I a i n   W i l s o n
-- 2010-12-27T23:03:36Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-12-27/queensland-declares-disaster-situation-in-areas-as-floods-inundate-state.html
Queensland declared a disaster
situation in some parts of the state in Australia’s northeast
corner as flood waters inundated several townships.  Emergency evacuations are currently underway in the
township of Theodore, Neil Roberts, the state’s minister for
police, corrective services and emergency services, said in an
e-mailed statement. More evacuations are expected.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Iain Wilson at 
 iwilson2@bloomberg.net  